is over $5 million,

02:55.875 --> 02:57.143
a little over
200,000 units.

02:57.143 --> 02:58.344
Corcoran: Wow!
Whoa!

02:58.344 --> 02:59.712
Greiner: Wait, wait, wait.
I didn't expect that.

02:59.712 --> 03:03.016
How did you sell
$5 million?

03:03.016 --> 03:07.921
Yeah, so, we started selling
them the summer of 2018 and --

03:07.921 --> 03:10.156
Okay. How much
did you sell in 2018?

03:10.156 --> 03:11.758
Little more
than $600,000.

03:11.758 --> 03:12.692
First year?

03:12.692 --> 03:13.593
Yes.
Wow.

03:13.593 --> 03:14.694
Okay. 2019?

03:14.694 --> 03:16.029
1.9.

03:16.029 --> 03:18.097
Wow.
Okay. 2020?

03:18.097 --> 03:19.699
1.3.

03:19.699 --> 03:21.401
Okay.
What happened there?

03:21.401 --> 03:23.436
The last couple years
have been downwards.

03:23.436 --> 03:25.538
We had $700,000
in the next year,

03:25.538 --> 03:27.874
and then last year,
a little more than $400,000.

03:27.874 --> 03:29.175
Ohh.

03:29.175 --> 03:30.877
So, what propelled you
initially

03:30.877 --> 03:32.478
to get that big bump
of sales?

03:32.478 --> 03:34.480
And then what happened
to slide them the other way?

03:34.480 --> 03:38.284
So, initially, the response
was really strong.

03:38.284 --> 03:41.588
A few famous people
had gotten their hands on them

03:41.588 --> 03:44.157
and had talked about them
on television and --

03:44.157 --> 03:45.959
Can you share who?
Sure.

03:45.959 --> 03:47.393
So, Hoda Kotb
went on the "Today" show

03:47.393 --> 03:49.395
and said they were
her favorite thing.
That's great.

03:49.395 --> 03:50.663
Two weeks after we...

03:50.663 --> 03:51.731
Launched.
...launched
our product.

03:51.731 --> 03:53.132
Wow.
We didn't know
she was doing it.

03:53.132 --> 03:54.434
-We had no idea.
-She didn't tell us.

03:54.434 --> 03:55.535
That's great.
That's great.

03:55.535 --> 03:56.903
And so to answer
your question, Mark, look.

03:56.903 --> 03:59.072
Stacy and I named the company
after our mother.

03:59.072 --> 04:01.341
Our mom's name is Bunny.
She passed away...

04:01.341 --> 04:02.575
-Aww.
-I'm sorry.

04:02.575 --> 04:03.776
Jenny: ...in 2008.

04:03.776 --> 04:05.712
And starting this company
and doing it in her honor

04:05.712 --> 04:07.947
was the first time,
after all these years...
Yeah.

04:07.947 --> 04:11.951
...we were able to say her name
and smile and have joy...

04:11.951 --> 04:13.786
Wow.
...instead of
just falling apart.

04:13.786 --> 04:16.289
Mm-hmm, so, then in 2020,

04:16.289 --> 04:18.691
like everybody
with supply-chain issues,

04:18.691 --> 04:21.160
we couldn't get our product
and our inventory.

04:21.160 --> 04:23.696
We couldn't get it right.
It was spotty.

04:23.696 --> 04:27.000
But on top of that, we also had
chemotherapy appointments

04:27.000 --> 04:28.735
we had to take our father to

04:28.735 --> 04:30.603
because our father
got diagnosed with cancer...

04:30.603 --> 04:33.039
-Oh, no.
-During the pande--

04:33.039 --> 04:35.208
...in the end of 2020.
Right.

04:35.208 --> 04:37.477
In all fairness,
the business did suffer

04:37.477 --> 04:40.246
because our energies
were diverted.

04:40.246 --> 04:42.348
And I'll let the -- I want them
to speak, too. I'm just...

04:42.348 --> 04:45.151
And on top of it,
we spent our time --

04:45.151 --> 04:46.986
we were redoing
our website.

04:46.986 --> 04:50.089
Coming out of the pandemic,
we were gonna put, you know --

04:50.089 --> 04:51.758
throw everything at this

04:51.758 --> 04:52.959
to come back strong.
Yeah.

04:52.959 --> 04:55.628
And the day we launched
our new website

04:55.628 --> 04:58.164
on Black Friday,
our dad passed away.

04:58.164 --> 04:59.465
That's the day
our dad died.

04:59.465 --> 05:01.134
Ohh. I'm so sorry.
Which year was this?

05:01.134 --> 05:02.902
-This past -- '22.
-This was the end of 2022.

05:02.902 --> 05:04.404
Jenny:
So, we lost our parents.

05:04.404 --> 05:06.806
We didn't lose the lessons
that they told us.

05:06.806 --> 05:08.241
We're not defined by, like,

05:08.241 --> 05:10.510
our biggest successes
and the greatest of the greats.

05:10.510 --> 05:13.279
We're defined by what we do
when things get tough.

05:13.279 --> 05:15.948
And we are resilient,
and we are at a point

05:15.948 --> 05:17.784
where we want to bring this back

05:17.784 --> 05:22.322
and reclaim what we had
and the momentum that we had.

05:22.322 --> 05:24.357
Alright, guys,
what are you making them for

05:24.357 --> 05:26.059
and what are you
selling them for?

05:26.059 --> 05:29.062
Our cost of goods landed
is about $3.70.

05:29.062 --> 05:30.863
The case
is another 60 cents.
Okay.

05:30.863 --> 05:33.166
And we sell them
for $35 and $40.

05:33.166 --> 05:35.001
-Wow!
-That's some good margins, yeah.

05:35.001 --> 05:37.403
Are you selling this primarily
direct-to-consumer...

05:37.403 --> 05:38.738
Yes. Yes.
...on your website?

05:38.738 --> 05:40.406
Are you selling through
Amazon, as well?
Andrea: Yes.

05:40.406 --> 05:42.108
Do you have
any other investors?

05:42.108 --> 05:44.744
We are self-funded.
We have zero debt.

05:44.744 --> 05:48.614
And we did recoup our initial
investment after year one.

05:48.614 --> 05:50.249
That's the only monies
we've taken out...

05:50.249 --> 05:52.919
So you guys are killing it.
I mean, well done.

05:54.087 --> 05:55.555
Why do you need a Shark?

05:55.555 --> 05:58.925
We need distribution.
We need big-box stores.

05:58.925 --> 06:01.594
We need other avenues
and channels.

06:01.594 --> 06:04.697
We want to make our reach as big
as possible because, look.

06:04.697 --> 06:05.898
Corcoran: Jenny.
Yes.

06:05.898 --> 06:07.500
Every entrepreneur
that comes in here

06:07.500 --> 06:09.168
wants their reach
as big as possible.

06:09.168 --> 06:10.737
They want
to be everywhere.

06:10.737 --> 06:14.540
What's your actual plan to
market them to get to your goal?

06:14.540 --> 06:16.142
Jenny:
The way we see this is,

06:16.142 --> 06:18.411
with the right channels
of getting the distribution,

06:18.411 --> 06:20.813
of getting the right displays
in the big-box stores --

06:20.813 --> 06:23.883
Because we know real estate in
these stores is very expensive.

06:23.883 --> 06:27.820
To show the functionality
of our Bunny Eyez, we believe,

06:27.820 --> 06:30.690
why would you want to wear any
other brand of reading glasses

06:30.690 --> 06:33.326
when these are, like,
the Transformer of glasses?

06:33.326 --> 06:36.129
So, guys. Look. This is
a very mature industry.

06:36.129 --> 06:37.296
Yes.

06:37.296 --> 06:40.466
And we have seen all kinds
of ideas in eyewear

06:40.466 --> 06:42.635
over the last 15 years
of "Shark Tank."

06:42.635 --> 06:46.005
We're all educated, and we know
there's a behemoth out there

06:46.005 --> 06:48.508
that provides
all of the frames...
Correct.

06:48.508 --> 06:51.043
...for everybody, everywhere,
all of the time.

06:51.043 --> 06:52.879
Have you gone to them
and said,

06:52.879 --> 06:55.681
"Look. You have
distribution everywhere.

06:55.681 --> 07:00.486
You provide an OEM service
to every brand in the world."

07:00.486 --> 07:01.854
You know exactly
who I'm talking about.

07:01.854 --> 07:03.055
-Exactly. We've had
a conversation...

07:03.055 --> 07:04.290
We have the answer
to your question.

07:04.290 --> 07:07.226
Okay. Yes or no. Are they
interested in licensing it?

07:07.226 --> 07:08.995
-W-We're in discussions.
-We're in discussions.

07:08.995 --> 07:10.630
-You are?
-Yes.

07:10.630 --> 07:12.098
And I was gonna
say to you, Kevin,

07:12.098 --> 07:13.633
because you're
the licensing master,

07:13.633 --> 07:16.235
that that was one option.

07:16.235 --> 07:18.004
It sounds like you've
already talked to them.

07:18.004 --> 07:19.172
I don't think
you need me.

07:19.172 --> 07:20.740
Very preliminary
stages,

07:20.740 --> 07:23.409
but we had one
preliminary conversation.

07:23.409 --> 07:25.912
Look, guys.
I'm not your Shark.

07:25.912 --> 07:28.281
I appreciate it.
I'm out.

07:31.150 --> 07:34.353
Okay. Look. Part of
the challenge to me is...

07:34.353 --> 07:36.956
You know, when Hoda wears them,
these TV shows,

07:36.956 --> 07:40.159
