television are trending older.

07:40.159 --> 07:42.595
So it's a great match
for what you're doing.

07:42.595 --> 07:45.097
Social media,
maybe some on Facebook,

07:45.097 --> 07:46.899
isn't as strong a match.
Jenny: Yeah.

07:46.899 --> 07:48.768
It's really interesting.
It's really cool.
Yeah.

07:48.768 --> 07:51.337
But it's still just a reader
at the end of the day.

07:51.337 --> 07:53.372
And it has to
be demonstrated

07:53.372 --> 07:55.208
to the
age-appropriate group

07:55.208 --> 07:56.542
that needs readers, right?
Sure.

07:56.542 --> 07:59.378
Which isn't as strong a match
to social media

07:59.378 --> 08:01.948
as I think you need
to really get that momentum.

08:01.948 --> 08:03.583
So for those reasons,
I'm out.

08:03.583 --> 08:05.318
Oh, come on back.
Aw, come on, Jenny!

08:05.318 --> 08:07.487
Come on back, Mark!
Come on, Jenny!

08:07.487 --> 08:09.789
Corcoran: I have to
be honest with you guys.

08:09.789 --> 08:12.825
I don't think you could sell it
in the retail space at all.

08:12.825 --> 08:15.027
I think you need someone to
show it, and that's a problem.

08:15.027 --> 08:16.295
It's really
the technology --

08:16.295 --> 08:17.864
I think it's gonna
be a huge challenge.

08:17.864 --> 08:19.699
And it's not one for me.
So I'm out.

08:19.699 --> 08:21.234
-Thank you.
-I agree with Barbara

08:21.234 --> 08:22.768
in a sense,
because when we said,

08:22.768 --> 08:24.537
"What are you gonna do
with the money?"

08:24.537 --> 08:26.405
one was in-store stands.

08:26.405 --> 08:28.841
