14:04.677 --> 14:07.279
Hi, Sharks.
Welcome to my classroom.

14:07.279 --> 14:08.514
My name is Brandi.

14:08.514 --> 14:10.983
I'm an ex-teacher
turned entrepreneur.

14:10.983 --> 14:12.751
Today's lesson is...

14:12.751 --> 14:14.920
why you should give me
a ton of cash

14:14.920 --> 14:16.956
so I can make you
a ton of cash...

14:16.956 --> 14:20.926
so together we can tackle
the literacy crisis in America.

14:20.926 --> 14:23.062
Sharks, when I was a teacher,

14:23.062 --> 14:24.930
my students
who struggled to read

14:24.930 --> 14:27.099
were frustrated
and embarrassed.

14:27.099 --> 14:29.802
I watched my students
turn from confident learners

14:29.802 --> 14:31.737
to thinking they were stupid.

14:31.737 --> 14:33.906
And I realized
that can follow a child

14:33.906 --> 14:35.441
for the rest of their life.

14:35.441 --> 14:38.177
So I decided to gamify reading
in my classroom

14:38.177 --> 14:40.279
to make it fun and stress-free.

14:40.279 --> 14:42.715
And the results were astounding!

14:42.715 --> 14:45.017
My students
who once struggled to read

14:45.017 --> 14:48.153
started devouring books
like hungry sharks.

14:48.153 --> 14:51.156
And that's why I created
The Fidget Game.

14:51.156 --> 14:53.492
This is not
your average board game.

14:53.492 --> 14:56.028
This is basically
a teacher in a box.

14:56.028 --> 14:57.997
My games are multisensory,

14:57.997 --> 14:59.632
aligned with the science
of reading.

14:59.632 --> 15:01.400
And they work!

15:01.400 --> 15:02.801
Here is how you play.

15:02.801 --> 15:04.770
First, a child chooses a card.

15:04.770 --> 15:06.071
If they get a heart card,

15:06.071 --> 15:08.207
it signals they need to
know the word by heart.

15:08.207 --> 15:09.441
They cannot sound it out.

15:09.441 --> 15:10.943
If they get
a lightning-bolt card,

15:10.943 --> 15:13.946
it signals they need to read it
in a flash by sounding it out.

15:13.946 --> 15:15.581
If the child says the word
correctly,

15:15.581 --> 15:18.517
they can roll the die,
pop the bubbles down on the mat.

15:18.517 --> 15:20.719
Whoever pops all of the bubbles
down first wins.

15:20.719 --> 15:22.087
[ Laughs ]

15:22.087 --> 15:24.323
So, Sharks,
I know you're probably

15:24.323 --> 15:26.859
nervously fidgeting
waiting for my offer.

15:26.859 --> 15:28.761
