an amazing business.

38:17.895 --> 38:19.830
You know, and it's obvious
what you need is help

38:19.830 --> 38:21.265
in expanding
that kitchen.

38:21.265 --> 38:23.067
I just don't know
anything about that.

38:23.067 --> 38:26.871
But I have no doubt
you'll figure it out.

38:26.871 --> 38:30.174
Congratulations on everything
you've accomplished. I'm out.

38:30.174 --> 38:31.976
Thank you so much.

38:31.976 --> 38:35.613
I promise you guys
that you'll never find somebody

38:35.613 --> 38:38.783
that's willing
to work harder than me.

38:38.783 --> 38:41.919
If you could use one word
that describes us,

38:41.919 --> 38:43.387
it's literally "clutch."

38:43.387 --> 38:45.623
[ Laughs ]
And when the time comes,

38:45.623 --> 38:47.892
four seconds left on the clock,
that's us.

38:47.892 --> 38:49.560
We make it happen.

38:49.560 --> 38:52.930
Alright. I'll give you
$100,000 for 25%.

38:52.930 --> 38:55.299
I'll do it for 20%.

38:55.299 --> 38:56.434
I'll do it for 15$.

38:56.434 --> 38:59.036
I'll do it
with Daymond for 25%.

39:07.545 --> 39:10.648
Narrator: Two sharks are out,
and there's a bidding war

39:10.648 --> 39:14.218
over Delson's dessert topping
company, Yum Crumbs.

39:14.218 --> 39:17.321
I'll give you $100,000
for 25%.

39:17.321 --> 39:19.023
I'll do it for 20%.

39:19.023 --> 39:20.358
I'll do it for 15%.

39:20.358 --> 39:23.527
I'll do it with Daymond
for 25%.

39:23.527 --> 39:25.029
We don't need her
in there.

39:25.029 --> 39:27.698
Yeah, but, you know, you
really do. Can I tell you why?

39:27.698 --> 39:29.900
I know the baking space,
and I'll tell you.

39:29.900 --> 39:33.437
You've got the magic thing
that most bakers don't.

39:33.437 --> 39:34.739
They can't sell.

39:34.739 --> 39:38.376
You are a phenomenal salesman
and hustler. That's unique.

39:38.376 --> 39:40.311
That's year
of selling cars.

39:40.311 --> 39:42.113
Yes, sir!
Yes, sir!

39:42.113 --> 39:46.417
Look. Just to squeeze heads,
I'll do it for 12.5%.

39:46.417 --> 39:49.920
I know this space inside out.
I know every commercial kitchen

39:49.920 --> 39:51.522
and toppings
in this country, okay?

39:51.522 --> 39:53.157
Because I did it
for Wicked Good cupcakes.

39:53.157 --> 39:54.425
Aw, yeah, yeah, yeah.
He knows everything.

39:54.425 --> 39:55.926
I think I could scale
your B2B.

39:55.926 --> 39:58.963
Delson, 25%.
Barbara and I.

39:58.963 --> 40:01.465
Barbara, are you
willing to partner?
Sure. Of course.

40:01.465 --> 40:03.567
I'll do it either way, but
let me tell you something.

40:03.567 --> 40:06.837
Barbara has a bake history
in Daisy Cakes,

40:06.837 --> 40:08.706
and she's been doing
this baking stuff

40:08.706 --> 40:09.907
for a long period
of time.

40:09.907 --> 40:10.908
Everybody has baking.

40:10.908 --> 40:12.176
I have a history
in the c-stores.

40:12.176 --> 40:14.044
Do you remember
Wicked Good Cupcakes?

40:14.044 --> 40:15.813
That's exactly one of the things
I was gonna say.

40:15.813 --> 40:18.282
Well, that's why I think I can
solve for this in two ways.

40:18.282 --> 40:19.683
But they weren't
in c-stores.

40:19.683 --> 40:21.352
Commercial kitchens

40:21.352 --> 40:23.354
and trimming down the number
of SKUs for B2C.

40:23.354 --> 40:24.889
Everybody's
gonna do that.

40:24.889 --> 40:28.225
Would you guys
do it for 20%?

40:28.225 --> 40:30.928
I would.
Would you, Daymond?

40:30.928 --> 40:32.396
Come on.
Yeah. Let's do it.

40:32.396 --> 40:33.998
Alright. Great.
Done. Deal!

40:33.998 --> 40:35.366
[ Laughter ]

40:35.366 --> 40:37.835
[ Sobbing ]

40:37.835 --> 40:40.371
Greiner: Good job!

40:40.371 --> 40:43.707
Greiner: Ohh! Oh.

40:43.707 --> 40:45.743
Corcoran: Ahh.

40:45.743 --> 40:47.211
♪♪

40:47.211 --> 40:50.481
My mom just passed away,
and...

40:50.481 --> 40:53.751
[ Sobbing ]

40:53.751 --> 40:55.719
Getting here is so hard.

40:55.719 --> 40:58.189
Come here. She's
looking upon you, man.

41:01.392 --> 41:02.927
Thank you so much.

41:02.927 --> 41:06.864
You guys don't understand what
this is and what you guys do.

41:06.864 --> 41:09.834
♪♪

41:09.834 --> 41:11.135
[Laughing]
I'm sorry.

41:11.135 --> 41:12.403
-Greiner: It's okay. It's okay.
-Cuban: Don't be.

41:12.403 --> 41:13.871
Delson: I said
I wasn't gonna cry.

41:13.871 --> 41:15.606
[ Sobbing ]

41:15.606 --> 41:18.275
Nothing stops.
Your mom passes. Whatever.

41:18.275 --> 41:21.445
The world just keeps spinning.
You gotta keep going.

41:21.445 --> 41:23.514
You gotta
put your emotions aside

41:23.514 --> 41:25.616
and you just
gotta make it happen.

41:25.616 --> 41:28.452
Your employees still have to get
paid. You know what I mean?

41:28.452 --> 41:30.654
Everything still
has to keep going.

41:30.654 --> 41:34.325
And that's why I know
this partnership --

41:34.325 --> 41:35.559
Barbara, my wife said,

41:35.559 --> 41:38.329
"Please don't leave there
without a deal," with you

41:38.329 --> 41:40.664
'cause she -- she said...
[ Cuban laughs ]

41:40.664 --> 41:41.932
No.

41:41.932 --> 41:43.033
John: All good.

41:43.033 --> 41:44.702
[ Laughter ]

41:44.702 --> 41:46.737
You've been through a roller
coaster of a lot, man.

41:46.737 --> 41:48.372
Oh, my kids, too.
Oh, my God.

41:48.372 --> 41:50.174
Hey, man. We're gonna be great
partners. Come in here, Barb.

41:50.174 --> 41:52.009
-Thank you so much.
-Come on. Threesome hug.

41:52.009 --> 41:53.010
Thank you so much.

41:53.010 --> 41:54.712
Cuban: Congratulations.
Congratulations.

41:54.712 --> 41:57.081
That's amazing.

41:57.081 --> 42:00.417
Yes! Ohh! Yes! Yes!

42:00.417 --> 42:03.220
[ Inhales deeply ] Whew!

42:03.220 --> 42:06.624
Ohh! Wow!

42:06.624 --> 42:09.126
Let's go!

42:10.628 --> 42:14.365
This is so crazy.
Everything we ever dreamed of.

42:14.365 --> 42:16.367
This is what's
going to happen.

42:16.367 --> 42:18.168
I'm so proud of you.

42:18.168 --> 42:21.272
Ohh! We did it.
We did it.

42:28.479 --> 42:29.513
Narrator: Next time, holiday
cheer comes to the tank...

42:29.513 --> 42:31.015
I love you, Santa!

42:31.015 --> 42:32.683
...and the Grinch is back.

42:32.683 --> 42:34.752
This deal sucks.
Oh-kay.

42:34.752 --> 42:36.420
I hate it
because it's seasonal.

42:36.420 --> 42:39.323
But if you ask any kid what the
holidays are truly all about,

42:39.323 --> 42:40.558
you know
what they'd say.

42:40.558 --> 42:42.059
All: Presents!
[ Laughs ]

42:42.059 --> 42:43.994
So, Sharks, who's ready
to really clean up?

42:43.994 --> 42:46.830
We're on the edge of
an avalanche of opportunity.

42:46.830 --> 42:48.899
We mortgaged the house.
Damn!

42:48.899 --> 42:50.467
You're hot stuff, really.

42:50.467 --> 42:52.269
You guys couldn't have
a more perfect background.

42:52.269 --> 42:54.104
Let's...wrap up
this deal.

42:54.104 --> 42:55.573
It's a Christmas miracle!

